sql:
SELECT grant_id, title, original_solicitation, recipient_id, award_number, amount, project_period_start, project_period_end, status_id
FROM grants
WHERE fiscal_year_id = 1;

SELECT status_name, description
FROM grant_statuses
WHERE status_id BETWEEN 1 AND 10;

SELECT recipient_id, COUNT(*) as Grant_Count
FROM grants
GROUP BY recipient_id;

SELECT grants.title, recipients.recipient_name, grants.amount
FROM grants
INNER JOIN recipients ON grants.recipient_id = recipients.recipient_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM grants 
WHERE fiscal_year_id = (SELECT fiscal_year_id FROM fiscal_years WHERE year = 2022);

external_knowledge:
Recent grants refer to those given in the fiscal year 2021;
Fiscal year designations are unique identifiers for each fiscal year;
The exact fiscal year is the historical period in which the grants were awarded and can be found in the fiscal_years table;
Report submission date is when the report was submitted and is found in the grant_reports table;
File locations are paths to the documents related to the grants.

- 'Treasures' metaphorically refers to significant or important grants awarded during the fiscal year 2022;
- 'Audit stories' encapsulates the findings and recommendations from the audit records;
- 'Voices' and 'latest whispers' metaphorically represent the `created_by`, `created_date`, `last_updated_by`, and `last_updated_date` indicating when and by whom these records were created and last updated.

sql:
SELECT SUM(amount) AS total_expenses
FROM grant_expenses
WHERE grant_id = 0;

SELECT amount 
FROM grants 
WHERE grant_id = 0;

SELECT g.title, gd.file_path
FROM grants g
JOIN grant_documents gd ON g.grant_id = gd.grant_id;
